    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For my days are consumed like smoke,.... Which suddenly rises up, is easily dissipated, and quickly disappears; so sudden, short, and transient, are the days of man's life; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "James 4:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or \"in smoke\" (c), as the Syriac version; his days were spent in great obscurity, in the darkness of affliction, temptation, and desertion; and in so much vexation, trouble, and uneasiness, as if he had lived in smoke all his time: and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "my bones are burnt as an hearth; on which fire is continually made for the preparation of food, and other uses: or as a \"trivet\", or \"gridiron\": so the Targum: or as a frying pan; so the Arabic version: the meaning is, that, through trouble and grief, his bones, the strongest parts of his body, the props and supports of it, were so weakened and enfeebled, the strength of them so exhausted, that they were as if they had been parched and burnt up, as the hearth by fire; see Proverbs 17:22. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "my bones are burnt as an hearth; on which fire is continually made for the preparation of food, and other uses: or as a \"trivet\", or \"gridiron\": so the Targum: or as a frying pan; so the Arabic version: the meaning is, that, through trouble and grief, his bones, the strongest parts of his body, the props and supports of it, were so weakened and enfeebled, the strength of them so exhausted, that they were as if they had been parched and burnt up, as the hearth by fire; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 17:22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
